transcript.text: Hello welcome to on print shop.
This video is about alignment rules under PDF block template.
In this video we will see when and how to create alignment rules.
There are two kind of alignment rules which we can create.
One is for horizontal blocks and one is for vertical blocks.
So alignment for horizontal blocks can be managed by creating virtual blocks.
Let us understand it by an example.
So here you can see there are multiple blocks in this template.
So there is a one block which we have converted into three virtual blocks where we have kept the name as city, state and zip code.
But let's say if someone will not, if a customer don't want to keep the state name and he want to remove it, so then Brooklyn should automatically take the place at the place of NJ.
So let's say if we have just removed NJ and click on update preview, so the Brooklyn is automatically taken the place at the state.
So this is horizontal alignment is already working.
Now moving to the next vertical alignment, when if we will remove the phone number and click on update preview, so there is a blank space.
So instead of this blank space, if we can move up for the fax, so it will be called as a vertical alignment rule.
So if the fax will be at the place of telephone, then this block will get empty.
So what we will do, we will keep the fax on the place of phone, then cell on the place of fax and the e-mail at the place of cell.
So how to create vertical alignment rules?
Just go to the admin, just go to the template section, product template and click on PDF block template.
So this one is our template.
Click on action, go to manage blocks.
So here which block we need to move in upper direction, let's say for facts, facts we want to move at the place of font.
So here we have to take this facts, just click on manage properties, click on add button, select alignment rules, select the reference block where we need to move this fax block that is phone.
And here we need to select vertical over here and just click on save.
So as we will click on save button here, if we go at front end and just refresh it, now if we will remove the phone number, the fax will automatically take the place at the place of phone number.
So here you can see in the same way we will move the cell to the facts and e-mail to the cell number.
So now we have created all the vertical arrangement rules.
If we will remove the phone number, all this block facts cell and e-mail will come up for just click on update preview.
So you can see all this facts cell and this has been moved in upper direction.
So in that way you can create alignment rules.
If you have any queries or concerns regarding this video, please connect with us at support@onprintshop.com.
Thank you.
